==English==
=== Noun ===
'''farce'''
#A low style of [[comedy]] or a [[dramatic]] [[composition]] marked by low [[humour]] & [[broad]] improbabilities and often written with little regard to regularity or method
#: ''The '''farce''' that we saw last night had us laughing and shaking our heads at the same time.''
#Abounding with [[ludicrous]] incidents and expressions
#: ''The first month of labor negotiations were a '''farce'''.''
#A [[ridiculous]] or empty show
#: ''The political arena is a mere '''farce''', with all sorts of fools trying to grab power.''
